@dingran thanks for double checking the results. We are now aware of that this might due to weight dropout with gradient clipping due to the gluonnlp's dependencies' version change. We are looking into it and will update once we got this right. It should not take long. At the meantime, please feel free to try the AWD pretrained model by using 
`        model, _ = nlp.model.get_model('awd_lstm_lm_1150', dataset_name='wikitext-2',
                                       pretrained=True)`
